1
00:00:00,080 --> 00:00:05,330
In this video we are going to see main benefits of API gateway pattern.

2
00:00:05,810 --> 00:00:08,840
So the API gateway pattern provides several benefits.

3
00:00:08,840 --> 00:00:15,050
Since we accommodate the client requests and route the internal microservices, we can handle main useful

4
00:00:15,050 --> 00:00:16,760
features into API gateway.

5
00:00:18,350 --> 00:00:21,980
The first feature is reverse proxy and gateway routing.

6
00:00:22,010 --> 00:00:24,290
This is part of gateway routing pattern.

7
00:00:24,290 --> 00:00:24,890
Features.

8
00:00:24,890 --> 00:00:31,250
The API gateway provides reverse proxy to redirect requests to the endpoints of the internal microservices.

9
00:00:31,280 --> 00:00:38,000
Usually it is using layer seven routing for Http requests for request redirection.

10
00:00:38,510 --> 00:00:44,210
This routing feature provides to decouple client applications from the internal microservices, so it

11
00:00:44,210 --> 00:00:47,240
is separating responsibilities on network layer.

12
00:00:48,360 --> 00:00:51,720
Another benefit is obstructing internal operations.

13
00:00:51,750 --> 00:00:57,900
API gateway provides abstraction over the backend microservices, so even there is no change on backend

14
00:00:57,900 --> 00:01:01,350
microservices, it won't be affect to the client applications.

15
00:01:01,350 --> 00:01:06,570
That means don't need to update client applications when changing backend microservices.

16
00:01:06,570 --> 00:01:12,570
Instead, API gateway will only change configuration file to redirect new services.

17
00:01:14,010 --> 00:01:19,410
And the second main feature is request aggregation and gateway aggregation.

18
00:01:19,440 --> 00:01:22,260
This is part of the gateway aggregation pattern.

19
00:01:22,260 --> 00:01:22,980
Features.

20
00:01:23,010 --> 00:01:29,880
API gateway can aggregate multiple internal microservices into a single client request.

21
00:01:29,970 --> 00:01:35,610
With this approach, the client application sends a single request to the API gateway.

22
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:42,510
After that, API gateway dispatches several requests to the internal microservices and then aggregates

23
00:01:42,510 --> 00:01:48,300
the result and sends everything back to the client application in one single response.

24
00:01:49,530 --> 00:01:50,160
The main.

25
00:01:50,190 --> 00:01:55,800
The main benefit of this gateway aggregation pattern is to reduce chattiness communication between the

26
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:58,020
client and the back end services.

27
00:01:58,820 --> 00:02:02,960
Another main benefit is cross-cutting concerns and gateway offloading.

28
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:05,840
This is part of the gateway offloading pattern.

29
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:06,470
Features.

30
00:02:06,470 --> 00:02:13,580
Since API gateway handles client requests in centralized places, it is best practice to implement cross-cutting

31
00:02:13,580 --> 00:02:15,800
functionality on the API gateways.

32
00:02:15,980 --> 00:02:22,520
The cross-cutting functionalities could be authentication, authorization, service discovery, integration,

33
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:29,360
response, caching, retry policy, circuit breaker and other operations for resilience, rate limiting,

34
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:35,420
throttling, load balancing, logging, tracing, correlation and IP listing, and so on.

35
00:02:35,510 --> 00:02:40,550
You can find the all cross-cutting concerns that can be handled from the API gateway in this list.

